HEADWORD: Lazarite
<hw>Laz"a*rite</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>One of
the <membof>Congregation of the Priests of the Mission</membof>, a
religious institute founded by <person>Vincent de Paul</person> in 1624,
and popularly called Lazarists or Lazarites from the College of St.
Lazare in Paris, which was occupied by them until 1792.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

